    • Constructor Detail

      • Car

        public Car(int velocity,
           int x,
           int y,
           java.lang.String imageName,
           Synchronizer sync,
           int id)
        Minimum Constructor.

        Sets the velocity of the car between 100 and 1000. Unlike standard velocity, a higher number is slower. This is because it is used as a length of time to sleep. This gives the appearance of faster/slower moving cars.

        Parameters:
        velocity - the integral speed of this Car
        x - the starting horizontal position of this Car
        y - the starting vertical position of this Car
        imageName - the filepath for this Car's image
        sync - the Synchronizer for this thread
        id - an arbitrary ID used for managing this thread
